Freddie resumability: every long-lived subsystem is an xstate machine with a durable persisted snapshot. src/machines/snapshot-store.js persists/loads xstate getPersistedSnapshot() into the machine_snapshots libsql table keyed by (kind,key) with schema_version + machine_id guards. src/machines/persistent-actor.js createPersistentActor rehydrates via createActor(machine,{snapshot}), auto-persists every transition, clears the row on final state. Kinds: agent (runTurn sessionKey, resumeTurn), batch (resumeBatch re-runs only unfinished prompts), cron (createCronMachine/startPersistentScheduler), gateway (lifecycle + gateway-msg in-flight), acp (lifecycle + acp-prompt). src/machines/resume.js resumeAll() runs on boot in src/web/server.js, src/cli/gateway_cli.js, src/acp/main.js to rehydrate interrupted agents/batches and surface lifecycle markers. GET /api/machines (plugins/gui-machines) exposes the live census.